Included files:
Makefile:
	make (or make lab0): creates executable lab0
	make dist: creates submission tarball
	make check: checks each option to see if no errors show up
		checks if --input and --output redirection work
		checks if --segfault and all it's variants work
		then removes created files and exits
	make clean: removes tar file and lab0 executable
README: this file
lab0.c: the source file for the whole shebang
backtrace.png: the gdb backtrace picture
breakpoint.png: the gdb breakpoint picture

Sources I used:
using system calls: https://www.ibm.com/developerworks/community/blogs/58e72888-6340-46ac-b488-d31aa4058e9c/entry/understanding_linux_open_system_call?lang=en
getopt_long example: https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Getopt-Long-Option-Example.html#Getopt-Long-Option-Example
How to change signal: signals: https://jameshfisher.com/2017/01/11/c-signal-unregister.html
